WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

2
00:01:20.357 --> 00:01:21.381
Six every touchdown.

3
00:01:21.559 --> 00:01:24.188
- But who keeps track?
- It's on the computer.

4
00:01:24.361 --> 00:01:27.354
Computer does everything. Every
stat gets converted into points.

5
00:01:27.531 --> 00:01:30.057
I don't know. Sounds
kind of dumb. to be honest.

6
00:01:30.234 --> 00:01:33.398
- I just wanna watch the game.
- You're afraid to lose 20 bucks.

7
00:01:33.571 --> 00:01:37.064
You wanna bet. let's do it. Why
mess with all this extra stuff?

8
00:01:37.241 --> 00:01:38.903
Trust me. it's fun.

9
00:01:58.562 --> 00:02:02.761
He's no longer in a coma.
but he's unresponsive.

10
00:02:02.933 --> 00:02:04.526
His condition is stable.

11
00:02:04.702 --> 00:02:06.694
They're managing
his blood pressure.

12
00:02:06.870 --> 00:02:09.430
But whether he will wake up...

13
00:02:09.607 --> 00:02:12.406
and understand what's
going on around him...

14
00:02:12.576 --> 00:02:14.374
there's no way of knowing.

15
00:02:14.545 --> 00:02:16.810
That's unacceptable.

16
00:02:17.247 --> 00:02:20.706
Gustavo. he's getting
very good care here.

17
00:02:20.884 --> 00:02:24.343
There's very little even
the best hospitals could do.

18
00:02:24.922 --> 00:02:26.550
Now...

19
00:02:27.124 --> 00:02:30.026
might it be different
if he was in the care...

20
00:02:30.194 --> 00:02:35.462
of some place like
Johns Hopkins. perhaps?

21
00:02:37.568 --> 00:02:39.264
Or...

22
00:02:40.471 --> 00:02:43.669
it could make no
difference at all.

23
00:02:45.309 --> 00:02:47.642
But in the end...

24
00:02:48.712 --> 00:02:50.840
In the end...

25
00:02:52.616 --> 00:02:55.609
I can think of no better
judgment on this man.

26
00:02:59.923 --> 00:03:02.449
Isn't this what he deserves?

27
00:03:03.427 --> 00:03:07.023
I decide what he deserves.

28
00:03:10.934 --> 00:03:13.199
No one else.

29
00:04:08.192 --> 00:04:09.387
There she is.

30
00:04:09.760 --> 00:04:11.922
Want some fresh OJ?

31
00:04:12.096 --> 00:04:15.692
Mm. Good. Vitamin C.
It'll help you heal quicker.

32
00:04:15.866 --> 00:04:17.767
I don't think it
works like that.

33
00:04:17.935 --> 00:04:20.029
Huh? It might. You don't know.

34
00:04:20.204 --> 00:04:21.900
I'm good.

35
00:04:22.072 --> 00:04:25.839
Oh. I've also got leftover bacon
from my breakfast sandwich.

36
00:04:26.009 --> 00:04:28.205
That's got definite
healing powers.

37
00:04:28.378 --> 00:04:30.040
Okay. that I believe.

38
00:04:30.214 --> 00:04:33.412
And I made coffee. put a
little cinnamon in it for flavor.

39
00:04:33.584 --> 00:04:35.610
Just trying something different.

40
00:04:35.786 --> 00:04:38.221
- You're up early.
- Yeah.

41
00:04:38.388 --> 00:04:41.119
- Oh. did I wake you with the noise?
- No. No. not at all.

42
00:04:41.592 --> 00:04:44.619
- I totally did. didn't I?
- No. I was getting up...

43
00:04:44.795 --> 00:04:47.321
- Sorry. I got job interviews lined up.
- Eventually.

44
00:04:47.498 --> 00:04:48.898
I wanted to get an early jump.

45
00:04:49.066 --> 00:04:51.331
I'm starting south. office
manager interview...

46
00:04:51.502 --> 00:04:55.405
in Polvadera. then I'm working
my way up north to Algodones.

47
00:04:55.572 --> 00:04:57.268
I got a lot of ground to cover.

48
00:04:57.441 --> 00:04:59.706
Jimmy. you know. you
can take some time off.

49
00:05:01.011 --> 00:05:04.607
Nobody's gonna ding you for not
having a steady job right this minute.

50
00:05:06.383 --> 00:05:07.407
Why wait?

51
00:05:08.552 --> 00:05:10.748
I don't want unemployment
hanging over my head.

52
00:05:10.921 --> 00:05:14.517
And we could use another
paycheck. and. uh...

53
00:05:15.159 --> 00:05:16.923
Besides. this is
your office now.

54
00:05:17.094 --> 00:05:19.893
- I don't wanna be a distraction.
- You're not a distraction.

55
00:05:20.063 --> 00:05:22.498
That's right. because I'll
be out finding me a job.

56
00:05:22.666 --> 00:05:23.827
Wish me luck.

57
00:05:24.001 --> 00:05:25.594
Good luck.

58
00:05:25.769 --> 00:05:28.568
- Oh. Thai or Mexican?
- Hmm?

59
00:05:28.739 --> 00:05:30.605
I'm gonna pick up
dinner on the way back.

60
00:05:30.774 --> 00:05:33.403
Oh. uh... Either. Your choice.

61
00:05:33.577 --> 00:05:35.341
And what a choice it shall be.

62
00:05:35.746 --> 00:05:38.147
Yeah. Okay. Jimmy.
wait. Are you...?

63
00:05:38.315 --> 00:05:40.147
You're not going
to that meeting?

64
00:05:40.317 --> 00:05:44.778
No. If there's anything important.
Howard knows how to find me.

65
00:06:38.876 --> 00:06:40.504
It's just me.

66
00:06:58.962 --> 00:06:59.986
Papa.

67
00:07:01.331 --> 00:07:02.355
It's over.

68
00:07:47.277 --> 00:07:49.405
You can keep that.

69
00:07:50.981 --> 00:07:53.382
No one's coming for it.

70
00:08:26.917 --> 00:08:28.146
Mijo.

71
00:08:31.621 --> 00:08:34.216
And when is it over for you?

72
00:08:35.792 --> 00:08:37.920
I'm working on it.

73
00:09:17.567 --> 00:09:18.967
Huh.

74
00:09:25.275 --> 00:09:27.972
You see there. that's
Alma. on the left is Ollie...

75
00:09:28.145 --> 00:09:29.511
Mr. Neff's aunt and uncle.

76
00:09:29.679 --> 00:09:32.478
They started this company
almost 50 years ago.

77
00:09:32.649 --> 00:09:35.016
- Whoa. Look at that.
- Yeah.

78
00:09:35.185 --> 00:09:37.347
And we think that other
fellow is Frank Corker.

79
00:09:37.521 --> 00:09:38.853
One of the early repairmen.

80
00:09:39.022 --> 00:09:41.753
They must've relied on him
a lot. That's a Thermo-Fax.

81
00:09:41.925 --> 00:09:45.418
It needed a specially-coated paper to
get an image off one of those babies.

82
00:09:45.595 --> 00:09:47.325
Oh. you know your stuff.

83
00:09:47.497 --> 00:09:50.433
I worked in a mail room. so
I talked to a lot of repairmen.

84
00:09:50.600 --> 00:09:52.694
- Heh. heh.
- A lot. They love talking shop.

85
00:09:52.869 --> 00:09:56.601
Yes. They are a
lonely bunch. for sure.

86
00:09:57.174 --> 00:10:01.339
This one was a real big seller
for Neff. really put us on the map.

87
00:10:01.511 --> 00:10:04.504
That's a 6500 color
copier. That's a warhorse.

88
00:10:04.681 --> 00:10:08.209
You ever see the guts of this beast?
It takes 15 seconds to get a printout.

89
00:10:08.385 --> 00:10:11.878
- I worked with one back in Chicago.
- That machine was almost too good.

90
00:10:12.055 --> 00:10:15.219
Counterfeiters used it
to make phony $5 bills.

91
00:10:15.392 --> 00:10:17.725
- What? That's...
- Yeah.

92
00:10:17.894 --> 00:10:20.454
- That's not right.
- Heh. heh.

93
00:10:20.630 --> 00:10:22.758
Oh. look. You got a lot
of hardware over here.

94
00:10:22.933 --> 00:10:26.233
Yes. Mr. Neff loves
sponsoring the kids.

95
00:10:26.403 --> 00:10:30.101
- Bowling. that's fun.
- We had a pretty good run in the '90s...

96
00:10:30.273 --> 00:10:33.402
but. uh. we don't find kids
much interested anymore.

97
00:10:33.577 --> 00:10:37.275
Yeah. this generation is all
hacky sack and video games.

98
00:10:37.447 --> 00:10:39.939
Ain't that the truth? Yeah.

99
00:10:40.784 --> 00:10:41.808
Hummels.

100
00:10:41.985 --> 00:10:44.318
Yes. Those were Alma's.

101
00:10:44.488 --> 00:10:48.050
She loved collecting the
little things. God rest her soul.

102
00:10:48.225 --> 00:10:51.491
- Yeah. I knew a lady. Same way.
- Hm.

103
00:10:51.661 --> 00:10:56.429
Ah. touring the wall of crap. I see. I
need to drag that stuff to the Dumpster.

104
00:10:56.600 --> 00:10:58.466
Haven't had a chance
to motivate myself.

105
00:10:58.635 --> 00:11:00.797
- Mr. Neff. James McGill.
- Just "Jimmy" is fine.

106
00:11:00.971 --> 00:11:04.635
Jimmy. Pleasure. Come
on down. have a seat.

107
00:11:05.175 --> 00:11:07.474
Guessing Henry filled
you in on what we look for?

108
00:11:07.644 --> 00:11:08.942
Oh. he did indeed. Um...

109
00:11:09.112 --> 00:11:10.808
Office-to-office salesman...

110
00:11:10.981 --> 00:11:13.712
willing to have multiple
doors slammed in my face...

111
00:11:13.884 --> 00:11:15.216
with one mission:

112
00:11:15.385 --> 00:11:17.217
Upgrade. upgrade. upgrade...

113
00:11:17.387 --> 00:11:20.152
their old copiers to your
top-of-the-line new ones.

114
00:11:20.323 --> 00:11:21.848
You think you have the chops?

115
00:11:22.025 --> 00:11:25.427
- It's a lot harder than it sounds.
- I'd sure love a crack at it.

116
00:11:25.595 --> 00:11:27.587
I'm told stubbornness
and persuasiveness...

117
00:11:27.764 --> 00:11:29.824
- are my top qualities.
- Heh. heh.

118
00:11:30.000 --> 00:11:32.265
I have to say. he knows
his way around a copier.

119
00:11:32.435 --> 00:11:34.028
No kidding.

120
00:11:34.471 --> 00:11:35.905
Well...

121
00:11:40.710 --> 00:11:43.270
Says here you were a lawyer...

122
00:11:44.748 --> 00:11:47.377
up until not that long ago.

123
00:11:49.085 --> 00:11:51.020
What changed?

124
00:11:51.655 --> 00:11:55.524
Well. you know why God made
snakes before he made lawyers?

125
00:11:55.692 --> 00:11:58.355
- He needed the practice.
- Ha-ha-ha.

126
00:11:58.528 --> 00:11:59.860
- Needed the practice.
- Yeah.

127
00:12:00.030 --> 00:12:01.191
Right?

128
00:12:01.364 --> 00:12:04.334
That's the only lawyer joke I
know because the others are true.

129
00:12:05.702 --> 00:12:09.161
Look. I know you're looking for
somebody with sales experience...

130
00:12:09.339 --> 00:12:10.807
and I don't have any.

131
00:12:10.974 --> 00:12:14.411
Except... Except being a lawyer.

132
00:12:15.011 --> 00:12:17.571
Look. being a lawyer.
my job was sales.

133
00:12:17.747 --> 00:12:21.115
I was selling the judges. juries.
sometimes I was selling the clients...

134
00:12:21.284 --> 00:12:23.844
to take the best deal from
a series of bad options.

135
00:12:24.020 --> 00:12:26.888
But every hour of every
day. I was convincing...

136
00:12:27.057 --> 00:12:29.526
persuading. I was selling.

137
00:12:30.694 --> 00:12:32.629
I hear what you're saying.

138
00:12:32.796 --> 00:12:36.733
We have a lot of high-ticket items
and a clientele primed to say no.

139
00:12:36.900 --> 00:12:41.770
Well. my spirit animal is a Gila monster.
and once I latch on. I don't let go.

140
00:12:41.938 --> 00:12:45.431
Ha-ha-ha. I like it. I like it.

141
00:12:45.909 --> 00:12:48.708
Well. you make a lot of
excellent points. Jimmy.

142
00:12:48.878 --> 00:12:51.279
I can see why Henry
wanted me to meet you.

143
00:12:51.448 --> 00:12:53.747
- Thank you for coming down.
- Absolutely. Anytime.

144
00:12:53.917 --> 00:12:56.853
We'll put our heads together.
have a decision in about a week.

145
00:12:57.020 --> 00:12:58.852
- We'll let you know then.
- Thank you.

146
00:12:59.022 --> 00:13:00.718
- You bet.
- Thanks. Great.

147
00:13:27.384 --> 00:13:30.616
- Yes?
- I'm sorry. can I have another minute?

148
00:13:30.787 --> 00:13:32.050
I'll be real quick.

149
00:13:32.222 --> 00:13:35.750
Yeah. sure. Jimmy.
What's on your mind?

150
00:13:35.925 --> 00:13:39.225
I know you're gonna take
time. consider your options...

151
00:13:39.396 --> 00:13:41.922
but maybe we can
settle this right now.

152
00:13:42.098 --> 00:13:44.897
There's a thing that we all
know called opportunity cost.

153
00:13:45.068 --> 00:13:48.505
The time you spend looking for
someone is time I could be working for you.

154
00:13:48.672 --> 00:13:53.201
And sure. there are salesmen out
there with way more experience than me.

155
00:13:53.376 --> 00:13:56.642
What are the chances one will walk
through that door in the next week?

156
00:13:56.813 --> 00:13:59.009
And is it worth the wait?

157
00:13:59.182 --> 00:14:00.650
Maybe. Maybe.

158
00:14:01.318 --> 00:14:03.651
But I can tell you this:

159
00:14:03.820 --> 00:14:07.120
None of them will have the
connection to your machines that I do.

160
00:14:07.290 --> 00:14:08.519
None.

161
00:14:08.692 --> 00:14:10.320
I worked in the mail room.

162
00:14:10.493 --> 00:14:12.621
I know how important
the copy machine is.

163
00:14:12.796 --> 00:14:14.822
Deadlines. last-minute changes.

164
00:14:14.998 --> 00:14:17.194
I was in there.
clearing paper jams.

165
00:14:17.367 --> 00:14:20.030
I was cleaning ink
off gears and rollers...

166
00:14:20.203 --> 00:14:23.901
trying to figure out where the
mystery streaks were coming from.

167
00:14:24.074 --> 00:14:25.804
I was down on my
hands and knees...

168
00:14:25.975 --> 00:14:28.604
with my tie over my shoulder
and ink-stained hands...

169
00:14:28.778 --> 00:14:32.874
and a line of assistants out the door.
all worried they're gonna lose their job...

170
00:14:33.049 --> 00:14:35.780
if they don't get their
document the next five minutes.

171
00:14:35.952 --> 00:14:38.547
I know... I know
better than anyone...

172
00:14:38.722 --> 00:14:43.023
that the copier. it's the
beating heart of any business.

173
00:14:43.193 --> 00:14:46.561
It goes down. it causes
delays. that is lost money...

174
00:14:46.730 --> 00:14:49.928
that is frustrated employees.
that's a negative work environment.

175
00:14:50.100 --> 00:14:52.365
That's a business
on life support.

176
00:14:52.535 --> 00:14:56.336
But you plug one of your new
machines into the system...

177
00:14:56.506 --> 00:15:00.500
whoo. that is a healthy.
strong heartbeat.

178
00:15:02.746 --> 00:15:04.715
That is a healthy business.

179
00:15:06.349 --> 00:15:08.750
That is a successful business.

180
00:15:08.918 --> 00:15:11.217
And that's what we're selling.

181
00:15:13.490 --> 00:15:14.924
Um...

182
00:15:16.393 --> 00:15:18.055
One minute.

183
00:15:25.668 --> 00:15:27.762
I don't need to see anymore.

184
00:15:27.937 --> 00:15:29.906
I mean. he's kind of exciting.

185
00:15:30.273 --> 00:15:33.471
He's great. I mean. the
passion this gentleman has...

186
00:15:33.643 --> 00:15:37.045
- Can you imagine sending that guy out?
- Yeah. Come on.

187
00:15:37.213 --> 00:15:38.408
Jimmy.

188
00:15:38.581 --> 00:15:40.106
Welcome to the team.

189
00:15:40.650 --> 00:15:42.710
- Really? 
- Damn right.

190
00:15:42.886 --> 00:15:45.583
Congrats. We'll get you
set up with Audrey in HR...

191
00:15:45.755 --> 00:15:49.192
fill out your paperwork. Hopefully.
you'll be all set by end of day.

192
00:15:49.359 --> 00:15:51.225
- Heh. heh.
- So just like that. huh?

193
00:15:51.394 --> 00:15:53.124
Why wait when we
can get you rolling?

194
00:15:53.296 --> 00:15:57.199
You were gonna take some
time. consider your options...

195
00:15:57.367 --> 00:16:00.531
but I just come in and did
that little song and dance...

196
00:16:00.703 --> 00:16:02.001
and I'm in?

197
00:16:02.172 --> 00:16:04.664
Yeah. Right. That's right.

198
00:16:06.042 --> 00:16:09.809
- Are you out of your mind?
- Heh. heh.

199
00:16:09.979 --> 00:16:11.572
You don't know me.

200
00:16:11.748 --> 00:16:13.376
I just came in off the street.

201
00:16:14.250 --> 00:16:15.946
You guys are like
a couple of cats.

202
00:16:16.119 --> 00:16:19.715
I come in. wave a shiny object
around. you're like. "I want that."

203
00:16:19.889 --> 00:16:21.721
- Heh. heh.
- No due diligence...

204
00:16:21.891 --> 00:16:23.655
no background check.

205
00:16:23.827 --> 00:16:27.457
No. "Just hire the guy that
says them fancy words."

206
00:16:27.630 --> 00:16:31.465
I could be a serial killer. I could be
a guy who pees in your coffee pot.

207
00:16:31.634 --> 00:16:33.398
I could be both.

208
00:16:34.204 --> 00:16:37.470
- So you're not taking the job?
- No. I'm not taking the job.

209
00:16:38.441 --> 00:16:40.239
Suckers.

210
00:16:41.377 --> 00:16:43.608
I feel sorry for you.

211
00:17:25.822 --> 00:17:28.587
Hello. Uh. I'm wondering.
are you still interviewing...

212
00:17:28.758 --> 00:17:31.523
for the sales
associate position?

213
00:17:32.395 --> 00:17:36.457
Great. I can be there
in. uh. 20 minutes.

214
00:17:37.767 --> 00:17:39.759
James McGill.

215
00:17:40.169 --> 00:17:45.039
Ellen. okay. Wonderful. Well.
thank you. Ellen. I'll see you soon.

216
00:18:08.164 --> 00:18:10.497
Pop-Pop. look how high I can go.

217
00:18:10.667 --> 00:18:12.693
Yeah. that's good.

218
00:18:12.869 --> 00:18:14.428
You be careful.

219
00:18:14.604 --> 00:18:16.368
You wanna do a couple more?

220
00:18:24.814 --> 00:18:26.339
Yeah?

221
00:18:27.584 --> 00:18:28.779
This is he.

222
00:18:32.622 --> 00:18:34.853
Meet at what time?

223
00:18:37.760 --> 00:18:40.958
Yeah. I can be there.
You let her know.

224
00:18:41.931 --> 00:18:43.627
Yeah.

225
00:18:44.901 --> 00:18:46.062
All right. baby.

226
00:18:46.235 --> 00:18:48.431
Time to get you
back to your mama.

227
00:18:48.605 --> 00:18:50.073
Five more minutes?

228
00:18:50.239 --> 00:18:52.333
- Oh. honey. come on.
- Please?

229
00:18:54.243 --> 00:18:56.303
Five minutes.

230
00:18:56.479 --> 00:18:57.811
You're on the clock.

231
00:18:57.981 --> 00:18:59.916
Thank you.

232
00:19:27.677 --> 00:19:30.670
- Good afternoon.
- Yeah. Madrigal Electromotive?

233
00:19:30.847 --> 00:19:32.873
Down the hall. the
Sandia Room on your left.

234
00:19:33.049 --> 00:19:34.415
- Thank you.
- Mm-hm.

235
00:19:48.364 --> 00:19:49.889
Oh. good.

236
00:19:50.066 --> 00:19:51.694
Take a seat.

237
00:20:13.990 --> 00:20:16.289
You didn't come all
this way just for me.

238
00:20:16.459 --> 00:20:19.486
I frequently travel to
conference with distributors.

239
00:20:19.662 --> 00:20:22.962
- Albuquerque is one of many stops.
- Hm.

240
00:20:25.001 --> 00:20:26.731
Okay.

241
00:20:28.571 --> 00:20:29.732
I'm just...

242
00:20:31.240 --> 00:20:33.505
looking for an explanation.

243
00:20:33.676 --> 00:20:35.577
You steal an employee's badge...

244
00:20:35.745 --> 00:20:38.510
waltz through my warehouse.
interfere with operations...

245
00:20:38.681 --> 00:20:41.549
and strong-arm
my facility manager.

246
00:20:41.718 --> 00:20:42.879
Why?

247
00:20:43.052 --> 00:20:45.783
I'm on your books as
a security consultant.

248
00:20:45.955 --> 00:20:49.983
If I show my face in your warehouse.
it makes for a better cover story.

249
00:20:50.693 --> 00:20:53.754
Anyone ever ask
if I was there. I was.

250
00:20:54.097 --> 00:20:57.727
Plus. you had a few things that
needed correcting. so consider it a bonus.

251
00:20:57.900 --> 00:21:01.701
That's not the point. This is
meant to be a paper transaction.

252
00:21:01.871 --> 00:21:04.898
You sit at home and we pay you.

253
00:21:05.074 --> 00:21:06.838
Your own money.

254
00:21:07.210 --> 00:21:11.272
Doing what you did. the way you
did it. raises the threat of exposure.

255
00:21:12.215 --> 00:21:14.878
The way I see it.
it lowers the threat.

256
00:21:15.051 --> 00:21:19.216
Like I said. now there's a face to
the name that cashes the check.

257
00:21:22.425 --> 00:21:24.087
So...

258
00:21:25.361 --> 00:21:27.262
what's your plan. then?

259
00:21:27.797 --> 00:21:31.131
Madrigal has eight
terminals in the Southwest.

260
00:21:31.300 --> 00:21:33.633
One down. seven to go.

261
00:21:34.203 --> 00:21:35.637
Uh-huh.

262
00:21:36.038 --> 00:21:37.700
And...

263
00:21:38.207 --> 00:21:40.301
if I asked you to reconsider?

264
00:21:40.476 --> 00:21:43.105
I'd ask you to do the same.

265
00:22:01.130 --> 00:22:04.396
At the moment. you
have Gus Fring's respect.

266
00:22:05.067 --> 00:22:07.536
I'd want to keep
that if I were you.

267
00:22:42.271 --> 00:22:43.466
Hello. Hi.

268
00:22:43.639 --> 00:22:46.006
Sorry to interrupt.
Dr. Diseth...

269
00:22:46.175 --> 00:22:50.010
this is Dr. Maureen Bruckner.
just arrived this morning.

270
00:22:50.179 --> 00:22:52.410
- Nice to meet you. Hello.
- Dr. Bruckner.

271
00:22:52.582 --> 00:22:55.279
Dr. Bruckner is visiting
from Johns Hopkins.

272
00:22:55.451 --> 00:22:58.910
We're asking her to take the lead
with some of the more severe cases...

273
00:22:59.088 --> 00:23:01.990
- including Mr. Salamanca.
- Johns Hopkins?

274
00:23:02.158 --> 00:23:05.856
Yes. a generous grant came
through which allowed Dr. Bruckner...

275
00:23:06.028 --> 00:23:08.827
- to lend us her expertise.
- Only temporarily.

276
00:23:08.998 --> 00:23:11.991
I'm not here to
step on any toes.

277
00:23:13.836 --> 00:23:15.168
Okay. I...

278
00:23:15.338 --> 00:23:19.070
Our staff can help with the database
whenever you're ready to pull records...

279
00:23:19.242 --> 00:23:22.178
but I'm available anytime
if you have any questions.

280
00:23:22.345 --> 00:23:25.338
Thank you. Again. I
don't wanna step on toes.

281
00:23:25.514 --> 00:23:29.349
- We can comanage care. if you like. we...
- No. no. Uh...

282
00:23:29.518 --> 00:23:32.852
- He's all yours. Good luck.
- Thank you.

283
00:23:35.124 --> 00:23:39.084
Okay. Um... Well. I
will let you get to it. then.

284
00:23:39.262 --> 00:23:42.357
Let us know if there's anything
you need. anything at all.

285
00:23:42.531 --> 00:23:43.760
Absolutely.

286
00:23:43.933 --> 00:23:45.333
Thank you.

287
00:23:45.501 --> 00:23:46.867
Are you the family?

288
00:23:49.906 --> 00:23:51.704
Are you the family?

289
00:23:54.944 --> 00:23:56.640
- Yes.
- Sons.

290
00:23:58.681 --> 00:24:00.047
He's our uncle.

291
00:24:00.216 --> 00:24:01.912
I want to let you know...

292
00:24:02.084 --> 00:24:05.680
that your uncle has been getting
excellent care here at Lovelace.

293
00:24:05.855 --> 00:24:08.381
But we're going to try
something a little different.

294
00:24:08.557 --> 00:24:12.494
Look. when parts of the brain
are damaged by a stroke...

295
00:24:12.662 --> 00:24:14.631
those parts. they
cannot be repaired.

296
00:24:14.797 --> 00:24:19.201
Our job is to stimulate
your uncle's brain...

297
00:24:19.368 --> 00:24:21.428
and teach it to rewire itself.

298
00:24:21.938 --> 00:24:24.305
We are going to start
here with the legs.

299
00:24:28.210 --> 00:24:30.179
When did they get here?

300
00:24:31.047 --> 00:24:32.447
Mm...

301
00:24:33.382 --> 00:24:36.409
Don't worry. We're
still running things.

302
00:24:41.123 --> 00:24:42.455
Hello...

303
00:24:42.625 --> 00:24:45.595
- Are you family as well?
- Friends of the family.

304
00:24:45.761 --> 00:24:47.059
Okay.

305
00:24:47.229 --> 00:24:48.754
As I was saying...

306
00:24:48.931 --> 00:24:51.901
I'll return later with an
occupational therapist...

307
00:24:52.068 --> 00:24:55.334
to begin some electrical
stimulus. In the meantime...

308
00:24:55.504 --> 00:24:57.973
I'd ask that you
speak to Hector.

309
00:24:58.140 --> 00:25:02.305
Chances are. on some
level. he can hear you.

310
00:25:02.478 --> 00:25:06.939
The more you speak. the more
his brain will work to respond...

311
00:25:07.116 --> 00:25:10.484
and find pathways to connect.

312
00:25:10.653 --> 00:25:12.144
Okay? Good.

313
00:25:12.521 --> 00:25:15.582
We'll do everything we
can to help your uncle.

314
00:25:15.758 --> 00:25:18.023
Nice to meet you all.

315
00:25:30.806 --> 00:25:32.297
Speak.

316
00:25:55.131 --> 00:25:56.827
Don Hector.

317
00:25:57.867 --> 00:26:00.393
Everything is good
out on the street.

318
00:26:05.374 --> 00:26:09.675
All our men are keeping busy.

319
00:26:10.146 --> 00:26:12.308
Real busy.

320
00:26:13.049 --> 00:26:14.642
That's right. Don Hector.

321
00:26:15.051 --> 00:26:17.680
We're staying on
top of the count.

322
00:26:18.554 --> 00:26:19.920
It's all looking good.

323
00:26:24.794 --> 00:26:28.458
We had a problem with that
shit gang over on Lomas. but...

324
00:26:28.631 --> 00:26:30.827
we showed some muscle.

325
00:26:31.233 --> 00:26:32.997
Took care of it.

326
00:26:33.602 --> 00:26:36.504
No one wants to mess
with the Salamancas.

327
00:26:37.039 --> 00:26:38.063
No one.

328
00:27:03.466 --> 00:27:05.332
You look good. Don Hector.

329
00:27:06.368 --> 00:27:07.893
Real good.

330
00:27:08.838 --> 00:27:11.433
The doctors. they're
gonna fix you up.

331
00:27:18.314 --> 00:27:19.338
Yes.

332
00:27:21.083 --> 00:27:23.484
You're gonna get past this...

333
00:27:25.554 --> 00:27:28.547
and be stronger than ever.

334
00:27:59.822 --> 00:28:02.087
- Yes? 
<i>- It's me.</i>

335
00:28:02.258 --> 00:28:03.317
<i>Can we meet?</i>

336
00:28:03.492 --> 00:28:05.586
- Now is not a good time.
<i>- I'm in town.</i>

337
00:28:05.761 --> 00:28:08.230
I can easily meet
wherever's convenient.

338
00:28:08.397 --> 00:28:10.263
<i>Assume this is a secure line.</i>

339
00:28:12.201 --> 00:28:15.433
I spoke with your
security contractor.

340
00:28:15.604 --> 00:28:18.540
I explained the situation again.

341
00:28:18.707 --> 00:28:21.472
But he's going to keep
doing what he's doing.

342
00:28:21.644 --> 00:28:23.510
<i>I understand.</i>

343
00:28:23.679 --> 00:28:27.343
But what he's doing
makes no sense.

344
00:28:27.516 --> 00:28:30.384
- Do his reasons matter?
<i>- They do. if he's unreliable.</i>

345
00:28:30.553 --> 00:28:32.112
He is reliable.

346
00:28:32.655 --> 00:28:36.353
So I'm just supposed to let him
keep stealing my employees' badges?

347
00:28:36.525 --> 00:28:38.460
<i>I don't know where
he'll turn up next...</i>

348
00:28:38.627 --> 00:28:41.722
<i>what disruption he'll cause.
what mess I'll have to clean up.</i>

349
00:28:41.897 --> 00:28:44.128
<i>This isn't something
I want to worry about.</i>

350
00:28:44.300 --> 00:28:47.134
Then I suggest you
give the man a badge.

351
00:28:53.375 --> 00:28:56.709
Varga and Salamanca's man.
Colon. they came by in the afternoon.

352
00:28:56.879 --> 00:28:58.472
Nephews were
in his room all day.

353
00:28:58.647 --> 00:29:01.640
Bruckner saw him three times.
couple of specialists with her.

354
00:29:01.817 --> 00:29:03.945
They took him for a brain scan

355
00:29:04.720 --> 00:29:06.086
And?

356
00:29:06.755 --> 00:29:08.986
That's everything. No change.

357
00:29:50.766 --> 00:29:52.530
You want me back
at the hospital?

358
00:29:58.540 --> 00:30:00.099
No.

359
00:30:02.177 --> 00:30:03.975
Call Victor.

360
00:30:04.146 --> 00:30:05.910
Have him meet us.

361
00:31:06.508 --> 00:31:08.306
Just a few more.

362
00:31:08.477 --> 00:31:09.877
I know Chuck was thorough...

363
00:31:10.045 --> 00:31:13.209
but even I didn't think there was
gonna be this much paperwork.

364
00:31:13.615 --> 00:31:15.709
Having worked with
him as long as I did...

365
00:31:15.884 --> 00:31:19.343
I was actually pleasantly
surprised by his restraint.

366
00:31:19.988 --> 00:31:23.516
This is the agreement for the
transfer of property. as discussed.

367
00:31:23.692 --> 00:31:25.285
If you can initial here.

368
00:31:26.628 --> 00:31:29.393
And right down here.

369
00:31:29.565 --> 00:31:32.296
- Am I late?
- Kim. No. right on time.

370
00:31:32.901 --> 00:31:35.871
We were just finishing up
Rebecca's side of things.

371
00:31:36.038 --> 00:31:37.199
Hi. Rebecca.

372
00:31:37.373 --> 00:31:39.433
It's nice to see you again

373
00:31:40.008 --> 00:31:43.206
I'm sorry we didn't get a
chance to talk more at the service.

374
00:31:43.379 --> 00:31:46.508
Oh. I don't think anyone
felt much like talking.

375
00:31:46.949 --> 00:31:50.044
- Jimmy's not coming?
- I'm here on his behalf.

376
00:31:50.219 --> 00:31:52.279
And that should do it.

377
00:31:52.454 --> 00:31:56.050
I apologize for bringing us together
so soon after Chuck's service.

378
00:31:56.225 --> 00:31:57.989
Um. it's really my fault.

379
00:31:58.160 --> 00:32:00.095
Howard's being polite.

380
00:32:00.262 --> 00:32:01.992
Thank you. Julie.

381
00:32:03.265 --> 00:32:06.997
In any event. we thought
since Rebecca was still in town...

382
00:32:07.169 --> 00:32:09.866
better to talk through
the estate in person.

383
00:32:10.038 --> 00:32:11.097
Sure.

384
00:32:11.273 --> 00:32:13.242
Chuck left the
house to Rebecca...

385
00:32:13.409 --> 00:32:16.038
and as executor. I'll be
liquidating the property.

386
00:32:16.211 --> 00:32:19.773
Howard suggested. and of course. I
agree. that it would be the right thing...

387
00:32:19.948 --> 00:32:23.407
for Jimmy to go through whatever
survived and take whatever he wants.

388
00:32:23.585 --> 00:32:26.885
- I mean. anything with sentimental value.
- We can set up a time.

389
00:32:27.055 --> 00:32:30.617
The estate can provide a truck and
storage for anything he chooses to keep.

390
00:32:30.793 --> 00:32:32.022
That's okay.

391
00:32:32.194 --> 00:32:33.924
Jimmy doesn't want any of it.

392
00:32:34.596 --> 00:32:35.620
You sure?

393
00:32:35.798 --> 00:32:39.200
I think the garage is pretty intact.
except for some water damage.

394
00:32:39.368 --> 00:32:42.099
He doesn't want it. Thank you.

395
00:32:44.072 --> 00:32:47.600
Okay. I understand. Ahem.

396
00:32:47.776 --> 00:32:49.608
Well. then...

397
00:32:49.778 --> 00:32:51.371
as far as Jimmy's concerned...

398
00:32:51.547 --> 00:32:54.517
all that's left is for him to
sign this agreement letter.

399
00:32:54.683 --> 00:32:59.121
Once that's done. we can
disperse his share of the estate.

400
00:32:59.288 --> 00:33:01.655
Let me guess. 4 thousand?

401
00:33:03.725 --> 00:33:05.057
Five.

402
00:33:06.495 --> 00:33:10.227
It's what you give when you cut someone
from a will and not have it contested.

403
00:33:10.399 --> 00:33:13.733
Just enough money to show
the recipient wasn't forgotten.

404
00:33:14.269 --> 00:33:19.173
Chuck also left a substantial endowment
for a scholarship for deserving youth.

405
00:33:19.341 --> 00:33:22.334
I was hoping Jimmy would
agree to serve on the board.

406
00:33:24.079 --> 00:33:25.945
I'll let him know.

407
00:33:26.114 --> 00:33:27.138
What else?

408
00:33:28.083 --> 00:33:29.608
Well...

409
00:33:30.152 --> 00:33:32.917
Chuck left Jimmy
a personal letter.

410
00:33:33.956 --> 00:33:35.720
His eyes only.

411
00:33:44.867 --> 00:33:48.269
Howard. thank you for
everything that you've done.

412
00:33:48.437 --> 00:33:50.099
I know it's been difficult.

413
00:33:50.272 --> 00:33:52.798
It's hard on all of us.

414
00:33:53.342 --> 00:33:56.608
Well. I don't wanna keep
you. Let me walk you out.

415
00:33:56.778 --> 00:34:00.306
Actually. Howard. we have
a few more things to discuss.

416
00:34:00.983 --> 00:34:05.182
Uh. Kim. please
give Jimmy my best.

417
00:34:06.288 --> 00:34:07.722
I will.

418
00:34:07.890 --> 00:34:10.018
It was very nice
seeing you. Rebecca.

419
00:34:10.192 --> 00:34:11.751
You too.

420
00:34:14.329 --> 00:34:16.298
- Safe travels.
- Hm.

421
00:34:21.303 --> 00:34:24.000
- Kim.
- I just. uh...

422
00:34:26.642 --> 00:34:28.508
I just...

423
00:34:29.711 --> 00:34:31.680
had to know...

424
00:34:31.980 --> 00:34:33.915
what were you thinking?

425
00:34:34.917 --> 00:34:36.442
About?

426
00:34:36.618 --> 00:34:38.610
When you came to Jimmy...

427
00:34:38.787 --> 00:34:41.985
on the day of his brother's
funeral and laid that shit on him?

428
00:34:42.157 --> 00:34:44.922
That Chuck killed himself?

429
00:34:45.594 --> 00:34:47.586
What's wrong with you?

430
00:34:48.430 --> 00:34:50.524
I thought...

431
00:34:50.866 --> 00:34:52.459
Um...

432
00:34:53.068 --> 00:34:56.038
I thought I owed it
to Jimmy to tell him.

433
00:34:56.204 --> 00:34:57.729
Owed it to him?

434
00:34:58.707 --> 00:35:00.835
Did you owe it to Rebecca?

435
00:35:01.009 --> 00:35:02.773
You tell her your theory?

436
00:35:02.945 --> 00:35:08.407
That Chuck intentionally
set himself on fire?

437
00:35:10.586 --> 00:35:11.679
I guess not.

438
00:35:11.853 --> 00:35:14.288
I guess you just saved
that one for Jimmy.

439
00:35:14.456 --> 00:35:16.152
Kim. I didn't do
it to hurt Jimmy.

440
00:35:16.325 --> 00:35:19.386
- You did it to make yourself feel better.
- That's not what I was...

441
00:35:19.561 --> 00:35:23.157
To make yourself feel
better by unloading your guilt.

442
00:35:23.332 --> 00:35:26.427
Who cares what it does to Jimmy.
as long as Howard Hamlin is okay.

443
00:35:26.602 --> 00:35:29.697
- Kim. I don't think that's fair.
- Fair?

444
00:35:29.871 --> 00:35:31.601
Let's talk about fair.

445
00:35:31.773 --> 00:35:35.175
"Hey. let's let Jimmy dig
around the fire-damaged wreck...

446
00:35:35.344 --> 00:35:37.779
where his brother
died screaming.

447
00:35:37.946 --> 00:35:39.915
Let's let him pick up
a keepsake or two."

448
00:35:40.082 --> 00:35:44.383
That is so. so fair!
And did I hear you right?

449
00:35:44.553 --> 00:35:47.955
You want him to serve on the
board of a scholarship committee?

450
00:35:48.123 --> 00:35:50.752
A scholarship that Chuck
never in a million years...

451
00:35:50.926 --> 00:35:54.226
would've given to
Jimmy. Never! It is just...

452
00:35:54.396 --> 00:35:57.560
I mean... Oh. what's this too.
huh. Howard? What's in this?

453
00:35:57.733 --> 00:36:00.760
One last "screw you. little
brother" from beyond the grave?

454
00:36:00.936 --> 00:36:03.405
I'm really supposed
to do this to him?

455
00:36:03.572 --> 00:36:05.404
All right. Kim.

456
00:36:06.675 --> 00:36:08.769
What can I do to make it better?

457
00:36:11.146 --> 00:36:12.808
Nothing.

458
00:36:14.082 --> 00:36:16.574
There is nothing you can do.

459
00:36:17.386 --> 00:36:19.378
Just stay away.

460
00:36:44.312 --> 00:36:45.336
Hey.

461
00:36:45.514 --> 00:36:48.177
I hope you're hungry. I
bought way too much food.

462
00:36:48.350 --> 00:36:50.114
Uh. yeah. I can always eat.

463
00:36:50.285 --> 00:36:52.049
Counter or couch?

464
00:36:52.220 --> 00:36:54.689
- Uh. couch is good.
- Couch it is.

465
00:36:55.424 --> 00:36:59.691
If I remember correctly. in five minutes.
one of the classic movie channels...

466
00:36:59.861 --> 00:37:02.854
is showing <i>White Heat</i>
without interruption.

467
00:37:03.031 --> 00:37:06.024
The other is showing
<i>Jaws 3</i> with commercials.

468
00:37:06.201 --> 00:37:08.864
So a real <i>Sophie's Choice.</i>

469
00:37:09.037 --> 00:37:13.532
- It is <i>Jaws 3-D.</i> to be exact.
- Ah.

470
00:37:13.709 --> 00:37:16.474
But Cagney wins this one.

471
00:37:16.645 --> 00:37:19.205
All right. Hey. I got
us. uh. Thai iced teas...

472
00:37:19.381 --> 00:37:23.182
unless you want me to pour
you something less non-alcoholic.

473
00:37:23.351 --> 00:37:25.479
No. I'm good with that.

474
00:37:25.654 --> 00:37:28.385
So how was the job search?

475
00:37:28.557 --> 00:37:30.185
Pretty good.

476
00:37:30.358 --> 00:37:32.156
I got a couple leads.

477
00:37:32.327 --> 00:37:34.353
Actually. I got an offer.

478
00:37:34.529 --> 00:37:36.157
- Really?
- Yeah...

479
00:37:36.331 --> 00:37:39.893
but. uh. didn't
feel quite right.

480
00:37:40.068 --> 00:37:41.764
It was. uh...

481
00:37:42.170 --> 00:37:44.105
It just wasn't a perfect fit.

482
00:37:44.272 --> 00:37:48.573
But I think I might get a call
back on one or two of the others.

483
00:37:48.744 --> 00:37:51.873
Wow. that's a
pretty good first day.

484
00:37:52.180 --> 00:37:54.911
You know. somebody's
gonna be lucky to get you.

485
00:37:57.486 --> 00:37:59.079
How was your day?

486
00:37:59.254 --> 00:38:03.316
I just mostly stayed here.
trying to get organized.

487
00:38:03.492 --> 00:38:07.725
No pressure from Paige and Kevin.
but I gotta get back on the horse. right?

488
00:38:08.263 --> 00:38:10.095
You are right.

489
00:38:10.265 --> 00:38:13.429
And. uh. movie's about to start.

490
00:38:13.602 --> 00:38:17.596
So where is the remote?

491
00:40:07.048 --> 00:40:09.643
<i>I'm not available.
Leave a message.</i>

492
00:40:11.019 --> 00:40:13.716
Hey. it's me. Listen. I
got something for you.

493
00:40:13.889 --> 00:40:15.448
It's a job.

494
00:40:15.624 --> 00:40:18.526
I think you're really
gonna like this...

495
00:40:18.693 --> 00:40:21.060
so call me.

496
00:40:47.255 --> 00:40:49.281
We're taking six tonight.

497
00:40:50.458 --> 00:40:51.756
What?

498
00:40:51.927 --> 00:40:54.453
Six keys. It's what
the boss would want.

499
00:40:55.063 --> 00:40:57.294
You're gonna back me up or what?

500
00:40:58.900 --> 00:41:00.425
Yeah.

501
00:41:21.890 --> 00:41:23.825
Where's the rest?

502
00:41:26.995 --> 00:41:29.157
I only see five.

503
00:41:30.198 --> 00:41:32.565
That was a one-time only.

504
00:41:32.901 --> 00:41:34.335
Not the way we see it.

505
00:41:34.502 --> 00:41:36.471
That's the way it is.

506
00:41:39.341 --> 00:41:41.936
Salamancas get six.

507
00:41:42.243 --> 00:41:44.178
We're not leaving without six.

508
00:41:47.816 --> 00:41:49.682
Your boss isn't giving orders.

509
00:41:49.851 --> 00:41:51.911
He can barely
even open his eyes.

510
00:41:52.754 --> 00:41:54.916
I'm giving the orders.

511
00:41:56.624 --> 00:41:58.616
Take the five or
leave with nothing.

512
00:42:09.437 --> 00:42:11.338
Do you wanna go?

513
00:42:14.175 --> 00:42:15.803
You heard him.

514
00:42:17.012 --> 00:42:18.708
Six.

515
00:42:19.080 --> 00:42:21.049
Put it away.

516
00:42:22.784 --> 00:42:25.083
Do you really wanna do this?

517
00:42:59.854 --> 00:43:02.949
Yeah. that's what I thought.

518
00:43:33.888 --> 00:43:36.255
That's how you do it. We
had them pissing their pants.

519
00:44:13.261 --> 00:44:15.230
I know what you've done.

520
00:44:17.866 --> 00:44:20.097
The Salamancas...

521
00:44:20.268 --> 00:44:22.237
they do not.

522
00:44:22.871 --> 00:44:25.397
Do you understand
what I am saying?

523
00:44:34.282 --> 00:44:36.376
Look at me.

524
00:44:39.687 --> 00:44:41.952
From now on...

525
00:44:42.123 --> 00:44:45.890
you are mine.

